86
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,120
No amount is enough.

87
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,400
It's a matter of principle.

88
00:03:59,190 --> 00:03:59,750
Well,

89
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,910
that's just my opinion.

90
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:02,240
Ultimately, its up to

91
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,960
Zhao Jun.

92
00:04:05,590 --> 00:04:06,360
Jun,

93
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:08,840
don't blame me for being blunt,

94
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:11,000
but if the money is fair,

95
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:12,800
just agree.

96
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,150
Going to court

97
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:15,960
is not a good thing.

98
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,360
Nothing wrong with that.

99
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,240
Every citizen has the right

100
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,560
to use the law

101
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,680
to protect themselves.

102
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:22,830
Mr. Gao says that

103
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:24,160
all the time in class too.

104
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:26,510
Uh, I do tend to say that.

105
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,430
But honestly, the amount is significant.

106
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,000
Sometimes, a lawsuit

107
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,630
is just a bargaining chip.

108
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:35,830
Are you really not gonna reconsider?

109
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:36,870
No.

110
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:38,630
Not every worker

111
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,510
has a good aunt

112
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:40,360
like Fang Wanzhi

113
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:42,040
or a kind principal like you.

114
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:45,070
So I'd rather get nothing

115
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,920
than let them go unpunished.

116
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,240
Fang Wanzhi,

117
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:53,920
you think so too?

118
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,240
The hospital said

119
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:56,800
injuries like this

120
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,070
happen all the time

121
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,160
at that factory.

122
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,160
Instead of fix the risks,

123
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,800
they just throw money at it

124
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,070
and dodge responsibility.

125
00:05:04,430 --> 00:05:06,070
We can't tolerate it.

126
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,560
I was a factory girl.

127
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:10,510
This isn't about the money.

128
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:12,390
This is about the
dignity of every worker.

129
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:13,560
Even their lives.

130
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:15,950
Whatever Auntie says.

131
00:05:18,310 --> 00:05:19,000
Mr. Gao,

132
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,600
we've entrusted this to you,

133
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:21,630
it's your call.

134
00:05:21,950 --> 00:05:23,310
Please see this lawsuit through.

135
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:24,830
If this changes anything,

136
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,560
then working there

137
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,270
meant something.

138
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,240
Good girl.

139
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:29,600
Just like Wanzhi.

140
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:31,480
Everyone from Shenxian Peak

141
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:33,950
has grit.

142
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:40,920
This place is open 24/7.

143
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:42,430
Look.

144
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,680
We've got everything you could need.

145
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:46,270
Do you smell that?

146
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:48,480
The smell of good fortune?

147
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,800
Ms. Fang.

148
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:53,360
Ms. Pei.

149
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,040
Wishing you a prosperous opening!

150
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,070
Congratulations!

151
00:05:56,070 --> 00:05:57,240
Thank you!

152
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:59,120
Thank you, everyone!

153
00:05:59,310 --> 00:06:01,360
Hope you'll all support our business.

154
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,800
Sure thing!

155
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,510
Come on

156
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:05,040
Let me show you around.

157
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:06,000
Okay.

158
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,270
Get your daily essentials here.

159
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:14,270
You're trusting me with something

160
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:14,830
this big?

161
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:15,750
If it were bigger,

162
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,190
I wouldn't trust you.

163
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:21,360
Got it.

164
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,120
You're paying me?

165
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,070
Just room and board would be fine.

166
00:06:26,430 --> 00:06:27,510
That's against labor laws

167
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:28,830
and local rules.

168
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,560
But you need regular checkups.

169
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,750
No work if you're unfit.

170
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,160
I drafted an employment contract.

171
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:35,800
Take a look.

172
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:36,560
A contract?

173
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,390
How am I supposed to understand this?

174
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:40,870
My eyesight's failing.

175
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,830
And I didn't get

176
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:43,920
much schooling.

177
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:44,630
Well,

178
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:45,950
I'll explain it to you.

179
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,270
Thanks then.

180
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:47,870
My pleasure.

181
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,240
He agreed?

182
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,270
Yeah.

183
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,750
Three months' probation.

184
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,720
One cigarette,

185
00:06:57,070 --> 00:06:58,510
and the contract's void,

186
00:06:58,750 --> 00:06:59,680
plus penalty.

187
00:06:59,870 --> 00:07:01,270
The penalty is

188
00:07:01,270 --> 00:07:02,070
120% of his wages.

189
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,920
His pay

190
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,560
isn't high.

191
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:06,680
Should I raise it?

192
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:08,560
The higher the pay,

193
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:10,390
the bigger the penalty.

194
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,040
I doubt he'll pass

195
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,040
the probation period.

196
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:14,630
At the store,

197
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:16,430
he sees cigarettes all day.

198
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,190
By the way,

199
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,480
are there any lectures

200
00:07:20,510 --> 00:07:21,680
I can attend?

201
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,120
What?

202
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,310
Want a degree?

203
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,430
Not your business.

204
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:27,750
Just bored.

205
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:30,510
You're like me.

206
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,390
Can't stay idle.

207
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,800
An economics professor

208
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,600
from Shenzhen University

209
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,800
is giving lectures.

210
00:07:37,830 --> 00:07:39,750
It's actually aimed at alumni.

211
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,310
Lot of entrepreneurs attend.

212
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:43,190
There's one tonight.

213
00:07:43,390 --> 00:07:43,920
You in?

214
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,240
Everyone,

215
00:07:48,190 --> 00:07:49,070
our country

216
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,630
is about to

217
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:51,430
join the WTO.

218
00:07:51,870 --> 00:07:52,870
The WTO

219
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:55,360
is an international organization.

220
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,070
Joining the WTO

221
00:07:57,390 --> 00:07:59,310
means both opportunities

222
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,310
and challenges.

223
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:01,800
So I hope each of you

224
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,430
will take the lead in your companies.

225
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,630
We need to ride this wave.

226
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,680
Lady?

227
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:09,750
Excuse me?

228
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:10,600
Lady?

229
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,430
Shouldn't be wrong.

230
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:14,800
It's you.

231
00:08:15,310 --> 00:08:16,240
Remember me?

232
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,240
You're...

233
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,240
Seaside Eateries.

234
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,480
Tell Me Please.

235
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,360
Song request.

236
00:08:25,310 --> 00:08:26,240
Tell Me Please.

237
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,870
Alright,

238
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:28,950
that one.

239
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,070
I'll sing it.

240
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:31,750
♪Tell me please♪

241
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:35,080
♪How you so easily♪

242
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:39,240
♪Like an angel smiling back to me♪

243
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:41,080
And then I hugged you.

244
00:08:41,910 --> 00:08:43,320
It's you!

245
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,320
I remember now.

246
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,320
I was drunk.

247
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:48,840
I apologize.

248
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:51,480
It's fine.

249
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,320
That was one of my hardest times.

250
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:55,240
Your kindness

251
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,720
warmed my heart.

252
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,150
I've made peace

253
00:08:58,870 --> 00:08:59,840
with the past.

254
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,240
Soon after,

255
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,390
I found

256
00:09:03,390 --> 00:09:04,440
the one for me.

257
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:05,480
Really?

258
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:06,790
Oh,

259
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:07,720
she's here too.

260
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,240
(It's backwards.)

261
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,960
(Yeah, it's backwards.)

262
00:09:11,670 --> 00:09:12,360
(Like this.)

263
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,360
(Pretty nice!)

264
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,120
(You're wonderful!)

265
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:17,960
That's my wife.

266
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:18,910
Great, isn't it?

267
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,150
Lots of workers come to

268
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,200
night school.

269
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:26,750
Some bring

270
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,320
their kids along.

271
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:29,790
So the school

272
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:30,840
set up

273
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:31,720
a temporary nursery.

274
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,080
She teaches young kids.

275
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:35,440
Works at a kindergarten during the day,

276
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:36,720
and at night

277
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:37,960
works a second job here.

278
00:09:38,550 --> 00:09:39,200
She has to

279
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,600
handle all these kids.

280
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,790
That's tough.

281
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,320
She's got a knack.

282
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,270
Toys.

283
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:46,790
She says

284
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:48,120
a toy

285
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,120
can fix any kid.

286
00:09:50,270 --> 00:09:50,870
Right.

287
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:52,390
See?

288
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:54,270
What's this?

289
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:57,440
(Go ahead then.)

290
00:09:58,390 --> 00:09:59,200
(Give it a try.)

291
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:00,320
(Look.)

292
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:02,790
(I'm a wolf!)

293
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:04,320
(I'm gonna get you!)

294
00:10:05,150 --> 00:10:06,320
(Gotcha!)

295
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:07,600
Wanzhi!

296
00:10:08,790 --> 00:10:09,630
Wanzhi!

297
00:10:11,270 --> 00:10:12,390
Dad, you're back!

298
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:13,270
Yeah, I'm back.

299
00:10:13,670 --> 00:10:14,750
Brought you something nice.

300
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,510
What's it?

301
00:10:15,630 --> 00:10:16,080
Come here.

302
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,630
Fun, right?

303
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,440
Yeah.

304
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,240
Do you like it?

305
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:21,910
Yes.

306
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:42,910
You're home.

307
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,360
You're back.

308
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:47,480
How was the professor?

309
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:48,360
Good.

310
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:49,790
I'll attend a lecture

311
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:51,360
when I'm free.

312
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:52,600
Guess who

313
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,390
I ran into today?

314
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,440
Who?

315
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,600
Remember that guy

316
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:58,270
who asked me to sing

317
00:10:58,270 --> 00:10:59,150
Tell Me Please?

318
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:01,200
Gosh, you ran into him!

319
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,550
His wife

320
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,960
looks after the students' kids

321
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,910
by the classroom.

322
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,510
Seems like

323
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,240
he's doing pretty well.

324
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,910
Wait, what do you mean?

325
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,240
Listen.

326
00:11:16,670 --> 00:11:18,910
With the baby boom
since the new millennium,

327
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,390
the demand for toys

328
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,960
is through the roof.

329
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:24,000
But the toy selection right now

330
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:24,910
is narrow.

331
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:26,600
And quality is inconsistent.

332
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:27,790
That leaves us

333
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,240
with a lot of room to explore.

334
00:11:29,550 --> 00:11:30,720
Besides, the toy market

335
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,720
is not as crowded as fashion.

336
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,480
Competition is not fierce.

337
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:35,480
So...

338
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:36,200
So,

339
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,320
you want to get into toys?

340
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:41,080
Are you free tomorrow?

341
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:42,840
Do some market research with me.

342
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:48,550
(In November 2001,)

343
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:50,200
(China joined the WTO.)

344
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:51,720
(The rules of the WTO,)

345
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,030
(like an invisible hand,)

346
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,750
(moved Shenzhen)

347
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:57,630
(from low-cost manufacturing
to the global stage.)

348
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,960
(After a year of research,)

349
00:11:59,030 --> 00:12:00,270
(I decided to pivot.)

350
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,840
(I'm not gambling on luck.)

351
00:12:02,510 --> 00:12:04,720
(I'm declaring war on fate again.)

352
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:06,120
(I often traveled)

353
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,200
(between Hong Kong, China,
and Shenzhen,)

354
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,120
(and rarely saw Gao Xiang.)

355
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:11,670
(He was also busy.)

356
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,000
(Seemed really driven.)

357
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:15,960
(Many young people)

358
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,480
(are quietly gathering strength)

359
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,320
(and sharpening their edges,)

360
00:12:19,550 --> 00:12:20,630
(ready to pounce.)

361
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,790
Great seams.

362
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:24,320
Yeah.

363
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:27,030
Getting into the toy industry?

364
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,080
Sounds good.

365
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:29,840
Suits you.

366
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:32,120
But

367
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,440
there's not much I can do to help.

368
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,360
I only have a few connections.

369
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:41,630
These are

370
00:12:41,790 --> 00:12:42,720
our school's alumni

371
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:44,000
who are connected

372
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:44,790
to the toy industry.

373
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:46,360
My name should help.

374
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:47,750
Already talked to

375
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:48,510
the important ones.

376
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:49,910
Especially Mr. Li.

377
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:50,480
Li Chunhai.

378
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:51,030
He's

379
00:12:51,030 --> 00:12:52,080
in the toy business

380
00:12:52,150 --> 00:12:53,150
and has orders in hand.

381
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,080
Contact him first.

382
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,600
You're really making me wonder

383
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,030
if you're secretly investigating me.

384
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,600
Openly.

385
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,550
I'm hungry.

386
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:04,910
Let's grab a bite.

387
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:05,550
Sure.

388
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:06,320
I'm hungry too.

389
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,030
But I have

390
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:07,750
one rule.

391
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:08,790
If a student treats me,

392
00:13:08,790 --> 00:13:09,870
I have to pay.

393
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:11,240
Especially a female student.

394
00:13:12,510 --> 00:13:14,000
So you often

395
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,480
have meals with female students?

396
00:13:17,270 --> 00:13:18,080
Uh, no.

397
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,320
I've never had meals with them.

398
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:20,750
No need to explain.

399
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:21,480
No, really.

400
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,360
I haven't!

401
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,600
You were at our school

402
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:24,960
for lectures all day.

403
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,440
You're that female student.

404
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:28,000
Drop the principal act.

405
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:28,960
I'm not your student.

406
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,600
Fine, you're my teacher.

407
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,630
My student? Never.

408
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:33,790
Eat or not?

409
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:34,480
Whatever.

410
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:35,720
Of course. Let's go.

411
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,480
You really did teach me something.

412
00:13:40,510 --> 00:13:41,750
Never give up.

413
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:43,200
Eat more.

414
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:44,720
Thanks.

415
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,870
(So,)

416
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:50,390
(that's settled then.)

417
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:51,550
(I'm done)

418
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:52,630
(with your stuff.)

419
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,150
Who's that?

420
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:56,510
Sounds familiar.

421
00:13:56,550 --> 00:13:58,240
(Stay close, huh?)

422
00:13:58,870 --> 00:14:00,000
Yeah, it's familiar.

423
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,750
(Mr. Xu, this way.)

424
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:03,910
Mr. Xu,

425
00:14:04,270 --> 00:14:06,840
I really enjoyed drinking with you.

426
00:14:06,870 --> 00:14:08,600
Hey, you two,

427
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,870
